<TITLE>FG approves $1.2bn for Kano-Kaduna rail project Seeks fresh loan from China</TITLE>
<TEXT>
The Federal Government has approved US$1.2 billion for the construction of the Kano-Kaduna standard gauge railway project. 
 
Minister of Transport, Mr Rotimi Amaechi, disclosed this in Kano, on Saturday, when he visited Governor Abdullahi Ganduje at the Government House, Kano. 
 
According the the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), Amaechi said the Federal Government was negotiating with China EXIM bank to finance the project. 
 
We are negotiating with China EXIM bank and we are convinced that this negotiation will end by June, he said. 
 
The minister said the government would provide about 100 locomotives for narrow gauge rail that would run through Lagos, Kano, Port Harcourt, Funtua and Gombe to improve the economy. 
 
